Common Issues
1. No hashes captured

Check:

wrong interface selected
victim never triggered fallback
DNS successfully resolved the name
traffic segmentation / local firewall interference
2. Responder starts but no useful traffic

Make sure the victim is actually trying to access:

fake hostnames
invalid shares
unresolved UNC paths
3. WPAD traffic only

This is still useful and may indicate proxy discovery/auth attempts.

Security Impact

LLMNR poisoning can support:

credential exposure
offline cracking
relay opportunities
lateral movement preparation

Even without initial code execution, it can become an entry point into a larger internal attack path.

